To analyse the phase structure transformation of the mixed-halide perovskite crystals with increasing VHBr% from 0 to 100%, the XRD patterns of CH3NH3Pb(BrxI1−x)3 crystals are shown in Fig. 1(a), and the magnified patterns in 2θ = 27.5 −31° are shown in Fig. 1(b). According to the XRD patterns in Fig. 1(a), the CH3NH3PbI3 and CH3NH3PbBr3 crystals with VHBr% for 0% and 100% have a tetragonal phase structure with the I4/mcm space group and a cubic structure phase with the Pm3¯m\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
